    ns1:inpersonHours "62 horas (39.7%)"@es ;
    ns1:numberOfCredits 6.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation """This subject aims to provide students with a comprehensive education that will enable them to become active and empowered global citizens. Through an innovative program aligned with several Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), the goal is to transform students into innovative engineers and leaders capable of addressing current and future challenges.

In particular, it focuses on SDG 3, which aims to ensure healthy lives and promote well-being for all. Students will develop enhanced skills related to creativity and the design of sustainable solutions, considering technical, functional, and socioeconomic aspects. Teamwork, planning, organization, and effective communication will be encouraged.

Additionally, students are expected to be able to identify, formulate, and solve engineering problems, evaluating their impact on society and considering the necessary ethical and privacy considerations. This will contribute to SDG sub-goals 4.3, 4.4, and 4.7, which refer to ensuring quality education, increasing professional and technical competencies, and ensuring that students acquire the knowledge necessary to promote sustainable development.

Through this course, new learning opportunities are provided to students, equipping them with the skills needed to find lasting solutions to the problems that most affect them, in this case, in the field of health. The digital transformation of health will not only improve the efficiency and sustainability of current healthcare systems but will also have a significant impact on the health and well-being of patients and citizens in general."""@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Enero"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Septiembre"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Septiembre-Enero"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "62 horas"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000843/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """The objective of this course is to provide students with a comprehensive theoretical and practical understanding of the technologies and methodologies used in the design, development, and evaluation of telemedicine systems. The main focus will be on understanding how digital technologies can improve the delivery of remote healthcare services.
During the course, students will explore the various tools and techniques used in telemedicine, including videoconferencing platforms, electronic health records, connected medical devices, and data analytics. Ethical, legal, and security aspects of telemedicine, as well as technical and interoperability considerations, will be discussed.
In addition, students will have the opportunity to apply their acquired knowledge to create a telemedicine project. This project will be based on a specific topic defined at the beginning of the course, and students will develop it throughout the semester. The project will allow them to integrate theoretical concepts with practical application, applying their skills to design innovative solutions to improve remote medical care.
Upon completion of the course, students are expected to have acquired a solid understanding of telemedicine technologies and methodologies, as well as the ability to design and evaluate projects in this field. Furthermore, they will be familiar with the current challenges and opportunities in the field of telemedicine and will understand its importance in the digital transformation of healthcare."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/mf.cabrera%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/cecilia.vera%40upm.es>,
