<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93000843/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The course will be passed when a grade of 5 points or higher out of a total of 10 is obtained.
Progressive Evaluation
By default, students will be assessed through progressive evaluation. The final grade in progressive evaluation will be obtained by summing the grades corresponding to the different assessment activities, with the following weights:
Exam: 40%
Completion and presentation of mandatory group work: 50%
Attendance and participation in the collective work: 10%
The evaluation will check if the students have acquired the competencies of the course. To pass the course, at least a score of 5 out of 10 must be obtained in the completion and presentation of the group work, as well as in the written exam. Individual contribution to the group work will be monitored and considered as a requirement to pass the course.
Overall Evaluation
Students who wish to opt out of progressive evaluation must send an email through the course's Moodle to the course coordinator at least two weeks before the extraordinary exam period approved by the School Board for the current course and semester. In this case, it is necessary to complete the group work and its presentation to acquire all the competencies of the course, in addition to the final exam. The maximum grade that can be obtained in the overall evaluation is 90%.
Extraordinary Evaluation
The extraordinary evaluation will be carried out using the same evaluation techniques as the overall evaluation."""@es ;
